description: Starblast crossover
name: Speed-Lines

description:
Thanos is in an all out war with the God of Thunder. But Thanos seems to be able to take all that Thor can dish out even with the Power Gem. Thanos is able to gain the upper hand. Meanwhile, the Silver Surfer faces off against the Dark Valkyrie.

The Surfer defeats the Valkyrie with an energy blast. This distracts Thor who is now angrier than ever. Thanos tells Thor that he has grown weary of thier combat and retrieves a weapon of his own design. He fires it and traps Thor in an energy field, completely immobilizing him.

The Infinity Watch arrive with Doctor Strange but time is running out, the field won't hold for long.
name: Blood and Thunder, Part 10: Common Enemy

description: Originally printed in The Amazing Spider-man #9.
name: The Man Called Electro

description: SHADOW WAR, Milestone's first crossover event, continues from Xombi (1994) #0 in this extra-sized issue. In the aftermath of their battle with the Demon Fox, a depleted Blood Syndicate finds its most personal secrets revealed as Sideshow and Iota of the Shadow Cabinet descend on them. Plus, Brickhouse and Third Rail start something big, and more is revealed about the ancient spirit Kwai. Continues in Static (1993 DC) #8.
name: After The Fox

description: SHADOW WAR, Milestone's first crossover event, continues from Hardware (1993) #11. Donner and Blitzen of the Shadow Cabinet - two women, one with superhuman strength, the other capable of superspeed - recruit Icon for their battle with the Star Chamber. But they don't recruit Rocket. Continues in Xombi (1994) #0.
name: Shadow of a Doubt

description: Shadow Cabinet led by Dharma had to go against Star Chamber in order to prevent them from using Quantum Juice to enslave the world. Dharma assembled heroes from Dakota to face off against Shadow Cabinet. Dr. Nathan Flack was revealed at the creator of Quantum Juice and it was revealed that the big bang occurred purposely thanks to Dr. Flack and Dharma.
name: Shadow War
Needless to Say, The Party Broke Up

description: David Kim, your average guy-who-cannot-die, and his eerie lifestyle. Xombi is approached by the surreal TWILIGHT, and the serrated RAINSAW, both of whom want a piece of him!
name: Theatre Of Phantoms

volume.name: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles/Flaming Carrot Crossover

description:
Blood of Ten Chiefs 3 and 4 are devoted to the telling of Graywolf and Swiftspear's private hunting. It tells the tale of how Swiftspear became Two-Spear.
Graywolf sneaks back to the human village and claims their pride-token, one of the Wolfriders' wolfears. Swiftspear is healing from a prior incident, but swears vengence. He and Graywolf stalk a human hunting party outside the village after he recovered. The result is a slaughter, and Swiftspear is even able to kill the human who killed his bond-wolf. After the human hunter dies, Swiftspear claims the spear made of human hands and becomes Two-Spear from then onward.
This is a moment where the war between humans & elves has been confirmed, and the elves rise as triumphant inhabitants of their world.
name: TWO SPEAR

description:
STRYFE LIVES! With the body of Nathan Summers under his control, Stryfe begins his assault on Cable's life and friends! Only one hope remains for Cable- his parents, Cyclops and Jean Grey of the X-Men! And Cable's wayward son Tyler learns the truth of his father's origin- but can he survive Stryfe's ambush?

More questions are answered, as Cyclops and Jean join Domino in the search for Stryfe/Cable. Even more are answered as Tyler Dayspring probes Askani and learns of Cable's origins.

Notes:

  • Includes a pin-up of Cable by Tony Daniel.
  • Error: Page 2 has a speech bubble attributed to Zero when it should have been to Askani.
  • Error: Throeblood calls Apocalypse El Naban Sur instead of En Sabah Nur.

Synopsis

Tyler Dayspring can't help but feel proud of himself. Mr. Sinister has freed Stryfe from inside Cable's mind. Tyler has captured the electric embodiment of the latest Askani, which prevents her from warning Cyclops and Jean Grey. Just for kicks, Tyler demands that Askani relate the history of his father. Askani begins with the birth of Nathan Christopher to Cyclops.

At Camp Verde, Stryfe (in Cable's body) inspects himself in the mirror. He curses Cable for shaving off the goatee and hastily packs a bag. Siryn approaches him and asks if he is okay. The last she knew Cable had gone off to fight Sinsear. He assures her that he is fine before planting a deep kiss and then knocking her out with an intense telepathic blast. Rictor charges in and Stryfe shoots him.

In Xavier's Mansion, Jean Grey watches old home video taken by Madelyne Pryor. Cyclops joins her and she wonders if the two of them will ever be able to commit to each other as he and Madelyne Pryor had. Xavier moves in and offers his opinion that the two of them should be able to marry and have a family. The conversation turns to their seemingly failed offspring. Domino enters and informs the trio that Stryfe wasn't the son of Cyclops and Madelyne Pryor - Cable was and is.

Inside Tyler's sanctuary, Askani shows him Cable's origin. Cable arrived in the future as a baby with the techno-organic virus. Mother Askani - Rachel Summers - feared that the child wouldn't survive and ordered to have him cloned. Tyler is shocked that Stryfe, the clone, the child without blemish, grew to be the man that tortured Tyler and warped his brain. He wonders what his life would have been like knowing that his father was truly the son of Cyclops.

Domino convinces Xavier, Cyclops, and Jean Grey to head to Camp Verde, the home of X-Force and the most likely place Stryfe will go to get supplies. Upon arriving, Xavier hurries the group along, as he senses the psionic cries of people in the base. They rush in and find Siryn and Richter lying on the ground. Domino goes searching for clues while the mutants are cared for. She returns as Siryn awakens to tell about her odd encounter with Cable. Domino shows a file that has Cable's personal diary on it in which he ponders about the goatee he grew. The group realizes that Cable must have been possessed before and is now possessed again by Stryfe. As confirmation, Zero appears and asks the group to accompany to reset his parameters. He is conflicted as to how to proceed himself and instructs the team to kill Cable to negate Stryfe.

Stryfe himself, meanwhile, tracks and finds Tyler's hideout. He finds a very conflicted Tyler and takes his moment to attack.
name: Fathers and Sons, Act Two: Illuminated Knights

description: Presented in Valiant Vision (3D with glasses).
name: An Angry Light

description:
The Infinity Watch, Doctor Strange and the Silver Surfer have been captured by the trolls of Asgard and taken to Castle Grimlock, palace of King Geirrodur. They are to be sacrificed to a massive creature known as the Borgeddon. But the witch counselor notices Pip and that he has troll in his blood. They awaken Pip and tell him that as a troll he has the chance to fight to the death for his life. Pip is allowed to choose one of his companions to take his place. He choses Adam.  
 
Warlock is taken to the arena and given his opponent - Olik, the brother of Ulik. Warlock is not allowed to use any weapons or special abilities or Moondragon will be killed. Adam is easily able to defeat Olik while Pip carries out the plan Adam transfered to him through the Soul Gem. Before Moondragon is killed, the rest of the captors had been rescued, and they all manage to escape.
name: Blood and Thunder, Part 8: Trial

description:
Overview

In the climactic end to this six-issue storyline, all four devils get what's coming to them -- unfortunately, it may not be exactly what they expected, as Renute holds everyone hostage while a time-bomb ticks out their last seconds of life. All that and the return of the vampires!

Summary

Mantovani wakes up in Renute's headquarters, which is filled with Grendels who have been turned into vampires. Gloria watches from above, in secret. Renute sets Bixby against Calhoun, stirring up their mutual passions for Simone. Renute reveals that turning into a vampire made him hate all things Grendel...he began to acquire every important treasure he could, so he could destroy them all with an atom bomb. These treasures include the soon-to-be-reincarnated Hunter Rose in Simone's boy, not to mention the actual skull of Hunter Rose, and the Mona Lisa.

Hearing his plan, Bixby, Mantovani, Gloria, and Calhoun join forces and attack the vampires, Renute, and Dulac. Calhoun manages to defuse the bomb, but is killed. Gloria gets close enough to see the Mona Lisa up close, but dies as well. Bixby smashes the skull of Rose against Dulac's head, killing him, and Mantovani pulls out Renute's heart with his bionic hand.

Bixby took the boy with him back to the Amazon to find his future. Mantovani ent back to his private detective job, along with one particular treasure to hang on his wall.
name: Four Fates, One Finale

volume.name: Grendel Tales: Four Devils, One Hell

description:
The story begins with Salome returning to the world. It is revealed that she brought the Fallen to Zarathos. But the Fallen agree to stay away from Salome.

Meanwhile, Doctor Strange returns to his destroyed mansion of Bleeker Street with Vicki Montesi. He gets a message from Caretaker but doesn't understand. All of a sudden Salome attacks Dr. Strange. The Midnight Sons come to Doctor Strange's aid but are to late. Doctor Strange all of a sudden explodes into a mystic blast. Salome is close to defeating the Midnight Sons but is stop by a strange figure. He blasts Salome into the distance. The being then leads the Midnight Sons to Zarathos.
name: Siege of Darkness, Part 15 Sacrifice Supreme

description: Watchtower, Part 2 of 3. In this depiction of a potential future for the Dark Knight, Batman invades Tri-Corner, the area controlled by Vigil, Inc., the ruthless private security agency backed by the mayor. While searching for clues to its insidious private agenda, the Dark Knight discovers he is targeted by an army of Vigil's armored guards, who have him outgunned, outnumbered and out on a limb!
name: Watchtower: Part 2 of 3

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
1. Changes part 1 (text)
Victor finally gets his manuscript to the editor, Karen Potts, and it tops their distribution and magazine list.

2. Changes part 2 (comic)
Suentes reveals that Astoria had a miscarriage, not an abortion. He also tells that aardvarks are an allegory of power and it's the first time there are 3 that exist at a time. After he leaves, Cerebus asks the women who wants to die first!
name: Mothers and Daughters 28 : Changes

description:
Overview

It started out as the salvage job of a lifetime, but now Sean Averil and the crew of the ocean-going tug Electra have lost their ship and are stranded aboard the Chinese spy ship Wan Xuan with a self-replicating computer virus from outer space! Where do you hide when the very ship you're on is alive and trying to kill you?
name: Part 2 (of 4)

description:
Happy X-Giving! After the months of hardship, the team finally takes a breather. Which is the perfect opportunity for a marriage proposal!

"Mixed Blessings."

The X-Men gather for Thanksgiving. While the team rake leaves, goof off and play a competitive game of football, Scott and Jean reflect on their history; Jean has a proposal for him...
name: Mixed Blessings

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Sgt. Rowan finally gets some answers from MacReady about the true nature of The Thing. As more people on Stewart Island turn up dead and mutilated, clues lead to the American ship, the Gettysburg, docked in Wallace Harbour. Meanwhile, Jennifer's own little private hell gets a little bit smaller as she struggles with The Thing -- and her lover, Powell -- for control of her memories and desires. The series is written by David de Vries, who brings the kind of authenticity of dialogue and place only a native New Zealander can to the story.
name: In Sickness Or In Health

volume.name: Thing From Another World: Eternal Vows

description:
The Story begins with Wolverine recovering at Heather Hudson's house when Lady Deathstrike crashes through the side of the house with claws extruded ready to claim her heritage, Wolverine's adamantium bones. Lady Deathstrike attacks all in her way to claim her prize which includes, Puck and Heather Hudson. Wolverine unwilling to unshed his now bone claws tackles and wrestles with Lady Deathstrike to keep his friends save, during the battle between them both a gas line is ruptured which causes a small explosion sparked by Lady Deathstrike's exposed wiring. After recovering from the explosion Lady Deathstrike is distracted by Puck and Heather forcing Wolverine to finally extrude his claws subjecting himself to immense pain to protect his friends. Lady Deathstrike turns at the sound of flesh tearing and ripping and is shocked to find that Wolverine no longer has the adamantium in his bones and Wolverine continued to bleed from the wounds created by his claws.

Wolverine makes Lady Deathstrike a deal to spare his friends and she can kill him or if not that they can continue to fight and it will cost her. Lady Deathstrike approaches Wolverine to reach out to him and touch him before withdrawing in anger having felt cheated of her prize as well as Wolverine's words of her having sacrificed humanity for nothing. Lady Deathstrike leaves the house refusing to fight and kill Wolverine a dishonorable act in her eyes knowing that all she has left is her honor and nothing else. Wolverine watches her leave the house.

Lady Deathstrike upon leaving in the Limo that she had arrived is stopped by two other characters who also have been hunting Wolverine, Cylla and Bloodscream. They halt her vehicle and ask her why she did not kill Wolverine and if she will stand against them to kill him. Lady Deathstrike answers she no longer wishes his death but will not stop them two and so it ends and is the beginning of the next issue.
name: The Lady Strikes

description:
The Starblasters kidnap Uatu the Watcher, then install two thrusters on the Moon to push it out of orbit onto our planet. While Quasar and other Earth super-heroes gather to investigate the changes of the Moon, the Starblasters also kidnap Kayla Ballantine, actual owner of the Star Brand.

Wide cameos of super-heroes from all the World.
name: Once In A Blue Moon

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Benedict Asp interrogates Shondra Kinsolving about where "Hemingford Gray" came from and how she knows him. Bruce Wayne, using Hemingford Gray as an alias, beats up some of Asp's high class goons using an electrified cane. Wayne has dyed his hair red and wearing a monocle.

The Hood shows up on Asp's property after finding the surrounding town's citizens all dead. Wayne is held up at gun point by Asp's goons and the Hood jumps in and saves him. The Hood cleans up the fodder while Wayne moves on and finds Jack Drake near death and tortured.

Asp escapes with Shondra in a helicopter and Wayne goes to the town to try and find Alfred. Wayne proclaims his love for Shondra and pledges that he will find her.
name: Bruce Wayne, Part Three: Curse of the Bat
And slowly he begins to remember...

description: The newly revitalized Scarab is drawn by a disturbance on the astral plane to a small town in North Carolina where all the men have killed themselves and the women share a dark and horrific secret.
name: Moveable Feasts
Evil Woman!

description:
Part 3 of the 3-part 'Spilled Blood,'. The mastermind behind Bloodsport and Hi-Tech's recent Metropolis massacres takes center stage as the man called Bloodthirst declares war on Superman.

Notes:

  • Martha Kent gets a new hairstyle.
  • Triangle 1994 #1.
  • Chronological continuation from Action Comics #694.
  • Chronological continuation in Superman #85.
name: Bloodthirst!

description:
A group of corporative developpers have tested a neurotoxin in the rain forest. Their goal is to push away the restriction that exists concerning internationally protected species. No species, no restrictions. So they think.

Catwoman and a group of animal rights protectors are planning to cut short their plans at the world meeting that is going to be held in Gotham City this week. Then the notes containing the formula to the secret poison are stolen...
name: Animal Rites

description:
With Mordru out of the way, the Legion must travel to Baaldur and face Glorith in order to maintain the balance of power in the universe. Can the Legion defeat their longtime foe?

The Legion combats Glorith on her homeworld, quickly finding themselves overwhelmed as she summons armies from across time. Glorith employs a hit and run strategy, attacking various units of Legionnaires and utilizing her time abilities to age and de-age various Legionnaires as they strike - permanently. When she uses her powers on the reflective Devlin O'Ryan, Glorith's own power is turned against her. This allows the Time Trapper to return to continuity.
name: A Moment in Time

description:
Spider-Man’s sentence has been passed…and it’s execution! But will the Jury be able to commit Spidey to death while Venom is still at large? Mary Jane makes a pivotal decision about her health.

Spidey continues his battle with the jury and the final part event.
name: Trial By Jury - Part 3: Rough Justice

description:
When the archfiend Asteroth raises the dread Gothodaemon, Etrigan and Hitman must get past their mutual distrust if they're going to stand a chance against the infernal creature.

Note: One of the tombstones in the cemetery bears the name "Harvey Kurtzma...", though the name is partially obscured, this is likely a reference to the much lauded cartoonist and editor Harvey Kurtzman.
name: Hell's Hitman, Part Three: A Night in the Town

description: In Sin City, trust is a four-letter word. In spite of himself, Dwight finds himself in love with Ava all over again. There's only one problem... her husband. A man who has promised to kill her. In order to rescue Ava, Dwight must first get past the most dangerous chauffeur in the world, Manute. But, when you're friends with Marv, it's amazing how much help you can get for buying the beer.

volume.name: Sin City: A Dame to Kill For

description: Archer & Armstrong - enslaved! Drugged and mind-controlled by Armstrong's long-time rival, Mr. Duerst, Archer & Armstrong are doomed to a lifetime of servitude for the rich and powerful. But when Archer's neighbor Pamela launches a desperate rescue attempt, will she leave mess that's too big to clean up?
name: Prisoners Of The Macrobiotic Cult

description:
With alien technology salvaged from Project: Deep Freeze and secrets stolen from the X-O Manowar armor, the U.S. government is building a new fighting force. Now, the secrets of the universe's most powerful weapon are in the hands of the America's most potent fighting force. Together they are... the Armorines!

Although the date "Feb. 1993" is stated on the cover, the indicia give the date Jan. 1994
name: Unit, Corps, God, Country, Part 1

description: With Dr. Mirage and his wife Carmen on the Eternal Warrior's side, the hunt for the last of the cursed coins is on! But will Gilad be able to resist the charms of Mademoiselle Noire -- a woman no man can resist?
name: Desert Mirage

description: When Ivar accidently gets transported to the North Am in 4002 right in the middle of the Malev war, Magnus has to protect him from the Malevs who want to possess the secrets of time travel in “If This Is Tuesday, This Must Be…North Am?”
name: If This Is Tuesday, This Must Be... North Am?

description:
1st appearance:
Ravenus (alias Mr. Raven)
name: Ravenus

description:
Turok and company fight to save Regan and others from the Spider People and hungry and dangerous dinosaurs.

A little girl has been kidnapped by an ancient tribe known as the Clan of the Spider People led by Chichak Spine-Breaker. Turok has been brought in due to the appearance of dinosaurs in the area. As Turok and company set out to find the Spider People they are watched by the very ones they seek. Quickly Regan Howell and paleontologist Darwin Challenger are captured.

Once captured by Chichak he uses the Regan to taunt Turok and tries to kill Turok by using Darwin as bait for some hungry dinosaurs. Instead Chichaks plans are foiled by Turok when he kills the dinosaurs (with the help of Andy Howell and another dinosaur). His plans foiled Chichak escapes with the little girl and Regan. Turok sets out to find Chichak but he is badly injured by the dinosaur that died and fell on his leg in the previous battle.

All of this puts Chichak's leadership in question and it gets worse when the tribe sees a large dinosaur beast in the moonlight. Up to this point they believed they were in heaven but start to question it after the recent circumstances. Chichak tells them that their must be a sacrifice to make the heaven continue and offers up one of his own people whom has deemed unworthy.
name: New River Part 2: Soul Sacrifice

description: Bruce Zick resurrects the legend of Atlas and pits the mighty titan against the wrath of the gods.

Overview

As Luke leads the Rebel fleet on its escape to its new base on Hoth, the Rebels' new allies, the Mon Calamari, plan a diversion to help them escape an Imperial blockade. But the Imperials soon realize that the Mon Calamari attacks are a diversion for the real Rebel escape, and they set off with the intent of destroying the Rebels once and for all. Meanwhile, Han, Chewie, and C-3P0 take off in the Millennium Falcon to find an alternate escape route to Hoth, but what they discover is a seemingly impassable route that would take them dangerously close to a gigantic stellar flare!

Allen Nunis and Al Williamson himself retouch Williamson's original artwork and add some new art of their own, and Steve Buccellato adds the perfect color complement to the classic newspaper strip art. The new color cover is a Nunis space spectacular!
name: Race for Survival (part 1)

description:
How much can the world change in 75 years? Don't ask Cal Carson. He's spent three quarters of a century in stasis, but now memories of his membership in the original Danger Unlimited team are gone. Still -- he's pretty sure the alien Xlerii shouldn't be ruling the earth...!

Danger Unlimited provides all-new super-team action from the man who redefined the genre: John Byrne! Plus, a rollicking, exciting back-up series written by Byrne and illustrated by Kieron Dwyer, starring the pulse-pounding fighter for freedom: The Torch of Liberty! Fans of classic superhero comics won't want to miss this one!
name: The Phoenix Agenda, Part One: Rebirth; The Great Escape

description:
Overview

Dark Horse Comics #18 features part 2 of "Alien," John Arcudi's terrifying tale of a village ripped apart by the mysterious Night Reaper. Young Suom and his hunting party finally locate the beast, but it may be the last thing they ever do. In part 2 of "Droids," IG-88, the infamous battledroid, forces R2-D2 to help steal a spaceship in a daring escape from the Hosk space station. And finally, everybody on the streets knows that Tony Vincenzo always finishes a fight. In the taut conclusion to "Predator: The Hunted City," he gets his chance.

Her mother, the famous evangelist Sister Eugenia Overton, has been killed by a fire-breathing thing crawling through New York's sewers. Now Sister Ellen tells the press about this monstrous Leviathan, a biblical fury that no normal man can hope to stop!

The police are helpless against the menace. Can the Shadow defeat it? Maybe, but only after he takes care of his more pressing problem -- dozens of heavily armed gangsters in their hideout! This is one of the most exciting gun-battles ever seen in comics!

volume.name: The Shadow: In the Coils of Leviathan

description: A cold wind blows along the streets of Arcadia, and black-hearted people on both sides of the law shudder at its passing. Word is out: The X-killer is on the loose! Cross him once and you get a warning; cross him twice and you're dead.  The Llewellyn Brothers hire the Gambler to take out the X but, X gets the drop on the Llewellyn Brothers first.  The brothers dead the Gambler and X play a game of cat and mouse as they try to be the first to kill each other.
name: Fire and Ice part 1: Abandoned Hearts

description:
Still in deep space, Superman encounters Auron, the super powered clone of Guardian (first seen in Superman: The Legacy of Superman #1), who possesses some of Superman's DNA. Together they battle an alien malevolence, but Auron is felled by something far more insidious - something connected to Superman himself.

Notes:

  • "DC Universe 15" one page ad featuring two headlines from the Daily Planet (Green Lantern) and Gotham Gazette (Eradicator vs the Outsiders) and two magazine covers from Newstime (Aquaman) and HQ (Guy Gardner).
  • Triangle 1994 #7.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #86.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #696.
name: Massacre

description: Something strange is happening to Damien Kane. His body is turning against him, causing his eyes to burn like balls of molten metal and his body to twist and shriek like tortured cats. In his search to unravel the mystery behind these painful changes, Damien will run headfirst into government conspiracies, military cover-ups and…the Un-Men!
name: The Nature of the Beast

volume.name: American Freak: A Tale of the Un-Men

description: In the conclusion of the 2-part "Mysterious Ways," Saint Evelyn tries to use her healing powers to cure Maxine's wild ways, an attempt that leads to an improvement in...Lucy's condition. Also, Deputy Dan faces an unlikely foe.
name: Mysterious Ways Part Two

description: Young Arthur Curry battles a raging polar bear to save an Enuit woman destined to mean a great deal to the adult Aquaman. But the threat of the bear itself is child's play compared to the evil of Nuliajak, the mother of all sea-beasts, and her undersea devil hound. Plus, an appearance by Arthur's brother Orm, the man who would one day be Aquaman's greatest foe...the Ocean Master.
name: Snowball in Hell

description:
A "Knightquest" crossover, continued from BATMAN (1940-2011) #503. Batman is hot on Catwoman's trail, believing she's stolen a shipment of nerve gas, Meanwhile, Catwoman is herself in pursuit of the real terrorist. Continued in CATWOMAN (1993-2001) #7.

Jean-Paul is being dually tormented by the desire to conquer Catwoman, and his internal demons with Saint Dumas. As Jean-Paul attempts to be better then Bruce Wayne as the Batman, Catwoman is engaged in terrorist plots. The docks are on fire, and the police are closing in on the caped crusader and his quarry.
name: Dark Dance

description: With the lethal agents of Logos still in pursuit, Black Orchid and Sherilyn arrive in San Antonio, Texas, and stumble into a magical snare set by an ambitious adept in Native American mysticism.
name: The God in the Cage

description:
Catwoman is busted by Batman as she tries to use a decoy to draw out the thieves who stole the xyklon-c, a lethal nerve gas, intended to be used to get rid of the people and animals of the rain forest in order to clear the way to development. Problem is, the thieves, part of an animal rights movement, are intending, on their part, to use the gas in the building holding the convention of corporates here in Gotham City.

By stopping Catwoman, Batman might just have sent them to their death...
name: Body Chemistry

description:
"Reconstructing the deconstructed"

In part 1 of the 5-part 'The Teiresias Wars,' the new U.S. President is escorted into the bowels of the Pentagon where he witnesses a terrifying sight, an event that marks the renewal of an ages-old conflict between the impossibly ancient shapeshifting magicians, the Teiresiae, and the Builders, whose plan it is to recreate the Tower of Babel.
name: The Teiresias Wars, Part One: A Handful of Dust

description: Where have the real heroes gone? The world has been overrun with brooding antiheroes, sociopathic urban vigilantes and amoral existentialists! How could a confused culture take comfort...if not for the FIGHTING AMERICAN? The Fighting American - the classic American hero of the 1950s created by the legendary team of Joe Simon and Jack Kirby - is back in action in a slightly skewed tightrope thriller of sky-high adventure. Created to battle a Red Menace that no longer exists, the Fighting American takes on the bewilderingly different social and political threats of today. Battling whatever bizarre menaces crop up, the Fighting American tackles characters like the Media Circus, the pug-ugly Gross National Product and the deficit-spending Def Izzit...threats masterminded by the diabolical masters of the non sequitur, the Free Association. In the mid-1980s, Johnny Flagg was one of the most vocal foes of the Red Menace. Every day, he stood on the front lines of the media blitz battling Communist cadres with his muckraking daytime television talk show, Flagg Waving. Then, Johnny was gunned down by the minions of the evil Ivan "Poison" Brotski, leaving Johnny's frail and timid brother, Nelson, to carry on the fight.
name: Brothers' Keepers Losers Weepers

description: A heatwave and crimewive in Keystone at Christmas time means a very cranky Flash in "Christmas Rush".
name: Christmas Rush

description:
Driven mad by the destruction of his city, Hal Jordan hell bent on its resurrection cuts a swath through the remaining Green Lantern corp in his bid for more power. As he gets closer to Oa and defeats his fellow Corps men he adds their rings to his. All this and on Oa the guardians are forced to make a fateful decision to safeguard there very survival......reinstate Sinestro of Korugar as leader of the green lantern corp since he alone stands a chance of stopping Hal!

Hal Jordan once the greatest green lantern is full of rage as he flies off toward the planet Oa. As he gets closer he’s confronted by a series of lanterns, from Kehaan and Laira to Tomar Tu, Hannu, Jack T chance, Boodika and even Kilowog. With each fight his rage increases as he thinks about all he’s given to the corps, to the guardians and to the galaxy as a whole and all he has to show for it is a charred piece of land where his “life” once stood. He also adds each defeated Lantern’s rings to his hand, thus increasing his powers.

Meanwhile on Oa the guardians are confident that one of there servants will stop Jordan, Ganthet is the lone voice of reason pleading they try an alternate course of action as what they are trying will not work. With no plan of their own as Jordan is almost upon Oa and more powerful than ever they decide to do as Ganthet suggests.

As Jordan arrives the guardians make one finale plea for him to surrender his ring when he refuses and demands the power of the central battery, their midnight savior approaches and its revealed as….SINESTRO!!!!
name: Emerald Twilight, Part 2: The Present

description: The Eradicator from 'Reign of the Supermen,' along with Wonder Woman and Bloodwynd, guest-star as members of the Justice League join the fight against the enhanced forces of Meta-Tech. Meanwhile, Hawkman and Hawkwoman take the battle to the spirit plane in an effort to return to their own bodies and bring an end to Count Viper. Plus, revelations about Hawkman's new powers...and the truth about his never-before-seen mother!
name: War Cry!

description:
Ice and the Justice League battle her brother Ewald. Ewald has taken the throne away from her father and has raised giant Nomad warriors from the dead to battle the Justice League.

The climax of this story ends in a face-off between Ice and her brother. When Ewald's magical staff is broken it explodes. This apperently kills Ewald. This puts Ice in a Position to take over her family throne. She decides instead for a democracy for her people. In the end of this issue the reader finds out someone was pulling Ewald's strings but, it is not revealed who.
name: They Might be Giants!

description: The JLI's just about gotten used to Godfrey, the strange, silent alien giant with the incredible power to do literally anything. But there'll be no getting used to Godfrey's even more powerful family, whose arrival threatens the Earth with destruction.
name: Born of Man and Woman

description: The Martian Manhunter leads a team of New Blood heroes (introduced in the BLOODLINES Annuals) against the fury of Wildman, the victim of a previously undiscovered parasite attack who has been transformed into a giant, raging beast.
name: Saturday Night's All Right for Fightin'!

description: When the Kid befriends a kind but hardened hustler living in the bowels of Times Square, he learns a thing or two about real people's problems and experiences firsthand what real violence feels like.
name: Small Wages

description:
Kid Quantum joins the Legionnaires, just as several members of the team disappear after an encounter with Kid Psycho.

James Cullen, revived, returns to the Legion of Super-Heroes while something odd happens to Ferro, Apparition, Brainiac 5 and Gossamer.
name: The Astounding Return Of Kid Quantum

description:
Robin's two worlds continue to collide and his sudden disappearances and late-night adventures have Ariana wondering if he's seeing someone else. To complicate matters even more, Robin's search for Cluemaster inevitably leads him to the costumed vigilante Spoiler!

Robin having difficulty keeping his lives separate. Ariana thinks he may be seeing someone else. Robin learns that Electrocutioner, Cluemaster, and Czonk have escaped. He investigates and runs into Spoiler.
name: Clueless

description: Even as Wesley Dodds continues his probe into the horrifying history of the Brute, twin tragedies strike the Ramsey family.
name: The Brute: Act Three

description:
"The Kindly Ones" part 1! At last it has come--a conflagration of nightmarish proportions that will affect the future of the Endless and the fate of the Dreaming forever! Friends, foes and unexpected betrayers return in the last major story arc of THE SANDMAN!

This story presents the beginning of the longest, and the most pivotal Sandman-story arc.

The future of the Endless and the fate of the Dreaming will be affected by a nightmarish conflict. A surprising ending awaits.
name: The Kindly Ones, Part 1

description: Part 3 of the 3-part 'History Lesson.' Kathy and Lenny's witchcraft trial adjourns with madness and magic as Shade and HELLBLAZER's John Constantine fight for the future - a future in which the History Man and Kathy's unborn child cannot both exist.
name: History Lesson, Part Three: Cheap Gin, Hot Water

description: Part 5 of 5. The Enterprise's true timeline has been restored at last, leaving Kirk, McCoy, Uhura and Sulu trapped in the past by the same temporal terrorists who destroyed the Romulan Empire.
name: Time Crime The Conclusion: Seems Like Old Times

description: Superboy explodes onto the scene in his very own monthly series, and he's out to set the record straight - this is definitely "Not the Adventures of Superman when he was a boy in Smallville!" SB sets up shop in Hawaii and soon runs into some old friends, new faces, and the cyborg villain - Sidearm.
name: Trouble in Paradise

deck: Part of the Reign of Tomorrow storyline.
description:
Matrix, the Girl of Steel, realizes that Lex Luthor II may not be the noble soul he seems as she gets closer to discovering a terrible secret he's been keeping from her ever since Doomsday hit Metropolis.

Luthor explains his relationship with Supergirl as she visits Ma and Pa Kent.
name: Trial Run

description: Part 4 of the 6-part “D.O.A.” Valor decides that if he's going to die, his death should have meaning, and he sets out to stop a planet-wide civil war single-handedly. Plus, the Legionnaires embark upon an ill-fated mission to the past.
name: D.O.A. Part Four: Absolute Power
Things that Go Bump in the Night!
Seduction of the Innocent

description: Michael Cray travels to Baghdad for a suicide mission, but on the way he learns that a much darker force is at work--one that looks to awaken and consume the world!
Variant: Gold Cover
name: Epilogue

description:
The final part in Spawn's battle with the Redeemer, and the end of Simmonsville and Major Vale.

The homeless distract the Redeemer while Spawn recovers. As he fights, Spawn gradually realizes that his foes powers are being depleted. With a final blast, he downs the Redeemer, who is transported back to his heavenly creators. Afterward, Spawn returns to Simmonsville and destroys this reminder of a happier time. He accepts that sorrow and loneliness have become his fate.
name: Reflections Pt. 3

description: The secret behind the first Stormwatch team, Stormwatch Prime, is finally revealed as Battalion and his teammates fight their way through Gamorra Island to rescue their old teammates Sunburst, Flashpoint and Nautika.

Supreme is on TV. 
 Interviewed by Maxine Wislow, he reveals among others things, the origin of his god-like powers. 
But the talsking show is interrupted by another events: In Arizona, two super-group battle Quantum, the powerful mutant. 
Plus 2 pages of the Black and White story.
name: The Interview

description: Firearm infiltrates a military base to rescue a kidnapped young boy, only to discover the secret of Prime.
The life of 'Anything', in flashback. A promising football star, his life is effectively over when uncontrollable shapechanging powers turn on.
